author: Danny Moran | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Oregon State Beavers-Washington State Cougars kickoff set for 1 p.m. on Oct. 17
text:
Oregon State 's game at Washington State on Oct. 17 will kick off at 1 p.m. and air on the Pac-12 Network, the school announced Monday.
It will be the second week in a row the Beavers start at that time. Oregon State will play at Arizona this Saturday, where kickoff will also be at 1 p.m. That game will air on the Fox Sports 1.
The Beavers lost at home to Washington State last season 39-32 but beat the Cougars in their last trip to Pullman â€“ a 52-24 rout in 2013 .
Oregon State will play three of its next four games on the road after hosting three of its first four contests at Reser Stadium. After traveling to Arizona and Washington State, it will host Colorado and then play at No. 5 Utah.
-- Danny Moran
